title: post-pessimism

is it normal to have obsessively fantasized about having been aborted as a fetus in your teenage years? i cursed my mum for giving birth to me,. now such a thing seems almost unthinkable. i wonder what changed. i used to be a stubborn antinatalist and was convinced life could only ever be painful and tragic and that happiness itself is only teasing a much greater disappointment etc,, or that even worse - nothing meant anything and it was all just a drag and the only reason i didn't just kill myself was because i thought that would be equally pointless and terrifying knowing i was going to die anyway. i was wrong. not because of any lapse in logic but because i had projected my terrible circumstances onto the nature of being,, a cold lifeless environment had been normalized by everyone around me. i was told that i was the problem repeatedly, that i had no right to be depressed, i hadnt tried hard enough to like it, hadn't seen enough of this world yet,[^1] etc. i remember my dad, upon discovering my misery, condemned my distain for life, telling me Ã¯m in my golden years and that life was only ever going to go downhill from here, and all i ever dared to ask was "wait... if this is it then whats the point?"

